bio.singa.simulation.model.sections

Enum CellTopology

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CellTopology>
      • bio.singa.simulation.model.sections.CellTopology
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<CellTopology>

    public enum CellTopology
extends java.lang.Enum<CellTopology>
    The cell topology defines how the subsections are spatially organized. A subsection is considered inner if a membrane is enclosing the subsection, isolating it from outer influences. A subsection is considered membrane, when it separates inside and outside of a cell section. For example the nucleus region of the cell could have the following topologies: INNER: nucleoplasm, MEMBRANE: nuclear envelope and OUTER: Cytoplasm.
